- "shining stars" refers to schools with the highest attendance rates;
- "the sun of attendance rarely sets" means an average daily presence rate greater than 0.9 (90%);
- "the shadows of unexcused absences are scarce" means an average daily rate of unexcused absences less than 0.1 (10%).

- Attendance rate is calculated as the percentage of total days present out of total days enrolled;
- An unexcused absence is considered a significant indicator of potential truancy issues;
- The threshold of 90% attendance and 3 unexcused absences is often used to identify students at risk of academic failure.

- "Top three students" refers to the students ranked highest in terms of the number of absences;
- "Truants" are students who are frequently absent from school without a valid excuse;
- "Currently marked as truants" means their truant status is active.

