- 'Truancy rate' is the percentage of unexcused absences out of the total number of attendance records;
- 'Total students' refers to the total number of students enrolled in a school;
- 'Students with absences' refers to the number of students who have at least one unexcused absence;
- 'Average days absent' is the average number of days a student was absent, considering only the days for which there is an attendance record.

- 'blossoms' refers to students;
- 'garden of learning' refers to the school;
- 'unique identifiers' refers to `student_id`;
- 'total absences' is the count of 'A' in `attendance_code`;
- 'total presence' is the count of 'P' in `attendance_code`;
- 'absence rate' is calculated as the percentage of 'A' codes relative to the total number of attendance records;
- 'absent more than 10% of the time' refers to the condition where the absence rate is greater than 10%.

- "black sheep" refers to students who have been marked as truant;
- "wandered off the path of good behavior" indicates that the student has an active truant status;
- "absent without a valid excuse" means the `unexcused_absence` flag is set to 1.

- "attendance rate" is calculated as the percentage of attendance records that are not unexcused or suspension absences;
